High Stakes (1989 - USA)                                       aka Melanie Rose

Thriller

director . . . Amos Kollek
starring . . . Sally Kirkland, Robert LuPone, Sarah Michelle Gellar, Kathy Bates
 
http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0097507/


filmed at New York City, New York, USA

Sally Kirkland stars as a good hearted hooker named Bambi Rose in this odd crime drama from director Amos Kollek. Bambi is getting a bit long in the tooth, and is at the mercy of a sadistic pimp named Slim, who has his fingers in nearly every sort of crime imaginable. When a greedy Wall Street stockbroker shows up on her doorstep after being mugged, Bambi enlists his aid in ripping off Slim and saving her daughter from a life of vice. More interesting than the film is the cast, which, aside from including some fine performances from Kirkland and Richard Lynch, features such future luminaries as Kathy Bates and Sarah Michelle Gellar.
